title: For Sale:  Springfield M1 Garand .30-06 24 inch Semi Auto Rifles
location: North Carolina, North Carolina, United States
postcontent: Special Springfield Armory M 1 Grand, the serial Number 1552534 was manufactured in early May 1943, we have discovered that rifles in that serial number range were delivered to USMC in Camp Lejeune NC, and then shipped to the Solomon Islands for use with the newly formed Marine Raider Commando Units. After WWII this rifle was sent to US Depot, Anniston, Alabama, and was then issued to the Danish Navy during the Korean War (see the Navy Anchor on the Rear Sight). After the War it was returned to Anniston and eventually it went into the Civilian Marksmanship Program, this is when the present owner hand picked it. The rifle was such a great example of what a Historic M1 should be the owner went one step more, he sent the rifle to Dean Dillabaugh of Dean's Gun Restoration, where the rifle was completely restored, a new barrel was added, and all parts were hand polished by Dean using Genuine Mil-Spec Parkerizing, following the government Armory process that meets Mil-Spec Stnd-171. The stock was custom made and hand fitted, and the gas system being stainless steel will not Parkerize so it was finished with a baked on enamel coating. I will say one thing, this rifle is tight, the bore is bright and shiny, the fitting is flawless and the lock up is positive and it is one of the best looking M1's that I have had in my hands, and it is for all practical purposes is a brand NEW M1 and it also qualifies as a C&R Rifle. I can have this ship to your state local dealer if needed

title: For Sale:  **In Stock* BNIB Jimenez Arms Full Size LC-380 Pistol w/2 mags
postcontent: Don't forget to click on my Armslist store (towards the top right side of the posting).  I usually have close to 100 guns listed at very competitive prices.  Let's play "Who is the moron".  Here are your options:1. the idiot that lists on Armslist a used version of this firearm for $$$$ more than what I am asking for BNIB;2. the guy that pays that for the used one; or3. me for selling brand new fireams at such incredibly low prices.My wife picks #3 (but for totally unrelated reasons). This model is in stock.  Very hard to find.  The factory makes them once and a while, and when they do I get as many as I can.  Basically the same gun as the extremely popular 9mm J.A.9 full size pistol, but chambered in .380acp.  380acp is better for home defense as the .380acp round is less likely to over-penertrate.  The bullet (part that comes out the front of the barrel) in a 380acp round is the same size as a 9mm bullet.  American made with manufacter's lifetime warranty.  Includes two 13 round magazines.  Unless you weigh 400lbs, this model is probably to big and heavy for conceal carry, but it's great for home defense, and as a truck gun.  Has great sights, with the rear being adjustable.Model: J.A. LC380 Height: 4.75 inches Thickness: 1.25 inches Weight: 30 Ounces Length: 6.625 inches Barrel Length: 3.75 inchesThe flagship feature of the Jimenez Arms LC380 is its easy to use massive screw adjustable rear sight which is adjustable for windage and elevation. Other, higher priced, pistols do not offer this kind of flexibility. The high visibility front sight is another great feature which adds to a highly effective sight pattern. These features coupled with a last round slide hold open makes this pistol uncommonly accurate and a delight at the range.
